The Accumulation of light is the main indicator of the effect of plant photosynthesis. It is calculated by the Illuminance (Intensity of light) and illumination time.
The demand for illuminance varies from plant to plant. Plants with low illuminance can not be better photosynthetic, while excessive illuminance would sunburn plants.
Accumulation of Light (Accumulated sunlight): The total amount of light exposure. The unit is mmol.
Illuminance (Sunlight): Intensity of light. The unit is lux.
